The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Muzaffarnagar, June 1 (PTI): A Muslim wedding solemnised according to Hindu rites during a mass marriage is invalid and against Islam, leading Islamic seminary Darul Uloom Deoband has said.           
	The ruling came following protests after a Muslim couple, Akbal Ali and Trabunnisa, tied the knot according to Hindu customs at a mass marriage organised by an NGO yesterday.                  
	 Lucknow (PTI): A case has been registered against BJP Rajya Sabha member Kusum Rais husband, Rajesh Rai, and three others for allegedly misbehaving with and beating up three persons at his resort in Lucknow. Rai managed to flee from the police station, an officer said.                  
	 Haifa (PTI): Warship INS Brahmaputra, armed with the Israeli-made Barak missile system, has arrived on a four-day goodwill visit to Haifa to re-affirm Indias ties with Israel. The visit shows the importance India attaches to its relationship with Israel, the commander of the warship, Captain Philipose G. Pynumootil, said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): An association of private detectives has sought permission from states and Union territories to conduct sting operations to uncover illegal sex determination and female foeticide. The association said it was its social responsibility to catch doctors involved in the practice.                  
	 Pune (PTI): Deccan Queen, the countrys first superfast train connecting Mumbai and Pune, entered its 80th year, on Monday. The train had made its first trip on June 1, 1930, and is used by commuters who travel between the two cities daily for work. The British had named the train Blue Bird Baby.                  
	 Kathmandu (PTI): An Indian woman who was injured in a blast at Kathmandus biggest church last week, has died. With the death of Grihalaxmi Joshi, 47, the number of those killed in the blast has reached three, a news agency said. Joshi was from Patna.                                                                                                                           
